**Severity:** Critical

**OWASP Top 10 2021 Category:** Authentication

**Solution:**

To fix this issue, upgrade Apache HTTP Server to a version that is not affected by CVE-2013-3587. The latest version of Apache HTTP Server is 2.4.55.

You can download the latest version of Apache HTTP Server from the following link:

https://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi

Once you have downloaded the latest version of Apache HTTP Server, you can install it by following the instructions in the Apache HTTP Server documentation.

**Additional Recommendations:**

In addition to upgrading Apache HTTP Server, you should also:

* Review your server configuration files to ensure that they are not allowing unauthorized access to your system.
* Implement a web application firewall (WAF) to protect your website from malicious attacks.
* Regularly scan your website for vulnerabilities and fix any that are found.
